<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-44-0117 </DOCNO><TEXT>This patent describes a compensation device for deep-well drilling toolswith a transversely divided outer pipe, the pipe members of which canbe rigidly connected to one another by a screw thread and comprise adjacentend faces as stop faces which approach one another when the pipe membersare screwed together and move apart from one another during the unscrewing.The device comprises a spacing member which can be inserted radially,from the outside, between the end faces. The screw thread has a lengthof engagement which secures the firm connection between the pipe memberswithin the whole preset compensating range.</TEXT></DOC>